## BLoC pattern

```dart
// features/locations/presentation/bloc/location_state_event.dart
sealed class LocationStateEvent {}

final class LoadLocationStateRequested extends LocationStateEvent {
  final int locationId;
  LoadLocationStateRequested(this.locationId);
}

final class LocationStateUpdated extends LocationStateEvent {
  final LocationState newState;
  LocationStateUpdated(this.newState);
}
```

```dart
// features/locations/presentation/bloc/location_state_state.dart
sealed class LocationStateScreenState {}

final class LocationStateInitial extends LocationStateScreenState {}

final class LocationStateLoading extends LocationStateScreenState {}

final class LocationStateLoaded extends LocationStateScreenState {
  final LocationState data;
  final bool isStale;
  LocationStateLoaded(this.data, {this.isStale = false});
}

final class LocationStateError extends LocationStateScreenState {
  final Failure failure;
  LocationStateError(this.failure);
}
```

```dart
// features/locations/presentation/bloc/location_state_bloc.dart
class LocationStateBloc extends Bloc<LocationStateEvent, LocationStateScreenState> {
  final GetLocationStateUseCase _getState;
  final SubscribeToLocationUseCase _subscribe;
  StreamSubscription<LocationState>? _liveSub;

  LocationStateBloc(this._getState, this._subscribe)
      : super(LocationStateInitial()) {
    on<LoadLocationStateRequested>(_onLoad);
    on<LocationStateUpdated>(_onUpdated);
  }

  Future<void> _onLoad(
    LoadLocationStateRequested event,
    Emitter<LocationStateScreenState> emit,
  ) async {
    emit(LocationStateLoading());
    final result = await _getState(event.locationId);
    result.fold(
      (failure) => emit(LocationStateError(failure)),
      (state) {
        emit(LocationStateLoaded(state));
        _liveSub?.cancel();
        _liveSub = _subscribe(event.locationId).listen(
          (s) => add(LocationStateUpdated(s)),
        );
      },
    );
  }

  void _onUpdated(LocationStateUpdated event, Emitter emit) {
    emit(LocationStateLoaded(event.newState));
  }

  @override
  Future<void> close() {
    _liveSub?.cancel();
    return super.close();
  }
}
```

## Offline-first

Every read use case follows this pattern:
1. Try cache (Hive) first — emit immediately as `isStale: true`.
2. Try network — emit fresh as `isStale: false` on success.
3. Persist network response to cache.

## Screen pattern

Every screen handles 4 states explicitly: Loading, Loaded, Error, Offline (stale data shown with banner).

```dart
class LocationDetailPage extends StatelessWidget {
  final int locationId;
  const LocationDetailPage({super.key, required this.locationId});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return BlocProvider(
      create: (_) => sl<LocationStateBloc>()
        ..add(LoadLocationStateRequested(locationId)),
      child: Scaffold(
        appBar: AppBar(title: const Text('Counter')),
        body: BlocBuilder<LocationStateBloc, LocationStateScreenState>(
          builder: (context, state) {
            return switch (state) {
              LocationStateInitial() || LocationStateLoading() =>
                const _LoadingView(),
              LocationStateLoaded(:final data, :final isStale) =>
                _LoadedView(data: data, isStale: isStale),
              LocationStateError(:final failure) =>
                _ErrorView(failure: failure),
            };
          },
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}
```

## Dependency injection

Use `get_it` registered in `core/di.dart`. No global singletons.

## What NOT to do

- ❌ Don't use `print()` — use `package:logger`
- ❌ Don't mix navigation libraries (GoRouter only)
- ❌ Don't put business logic in widgets
- ❌ Don't catch and ignore exceptions
- ❌ Don't use `setState` in a screen that has a BLoC
- ❌ Don't ship a screen without offline + error states
